5000|$|Bailout valves - {{a device}} in the {{mouthpiece}} on the loop which connects to a bailout <b>demand</b> <b>valve</b> {{and can be}} switched to provide gas from either the loop or the <b>demand</b> <b>valve</b> without the diver taking the mouthpiece {{from his or her}} mouth. An important safety device when carbon dioxide poisoning occurs.|$|R
