25|$|The {{alternative}} is to donate the primary <b>demand</b> <b>valve</b> that the donor is currently breathing from, {{on the principle that}} it is known to be working and is immediately recognizable and accessible. The donor, who should be less stressed, will then switch to the secondary <b>demand</b> <b>valve,</b> which in this arrangement is generally mounted on a loop of bungee cord which hangs on the neck, and keeps the secondary <b>demand</b> <b>valve</b> tucked up under the diver's chin, where it can often be reached without the use of the hands, by bending the head forward and gripping the mouthpiece with the teeth.|$|R
